tee hee... i almost died laughing, probably because i am very tired but still... 



Ever since Aaron was poisoned, Mtv has been begging to put his house on
"Cribs".  But since Aaron lives in a heavily fortified bunker in Caracas,
they decided to pass.  So, they came crawling to me, the sweet Sister who
happens to be second in command.

I love Mtv Cribs because it lets regular people see how sad and desperate
their lives are.  They get to see mansions and wealth they will never
achieve.  I've always felt Mtv should do a show where they go to the slums
of Cite Soleil, Mumbai, and Bangalore. That way people could feel good about
their crappy rundown homes.
But I digress.

When the Mtv crew came to my house I was hoping they would send superstar VJ
John Sencio.  But apparently he's moved on to infomercials selling food
rehydrators, and transvestite workout tapes.  I'm just kidding.  He actually
works in my stable, and no I don't own any horses.

Instead, Mtv sent one of those new darling, interchangeable hosts of
indeterminate age, sex, and national origin.  They were very sweet but
overly hip.  After the third unwarranted use of the term "crunked", I ended
up beating him/her to death with a tire iron.  I don't know if they'll show
it in the episode because just as I landed the killing blow, my boob slipped
out of my halter top.  We all had a good laugh.

My house is kind of like the Playboy mansion, but with hotter chicks.  And
unlike Hef, I don't need to be lead by the hand around the grounds in a
stupor.  I also don't spend my days drooling, dressed in a tattered bathrobe
loosely slung over a pair of soiled Depends.  I don't allow girls with
breast implants on my property.  If they wander on, their implants are
forcibly removed and nailed to the wall as a warning to the next bimbo.
When they show this wall on '"Cribs" it's so covered with implants, it looks
like a sheet of bubble wrap.

The tour of the kitchen is unremarkable since my fridge is almost empty.
That's because I prefer to have all of my food prepared fresh.
Specifically, I want to watch it die before I eat it.  Nothing makes a meal
more memorable than thinking about that moment, the look on the animal's
face as the cold blade touches their neck for the first time.   Never has
a piece of veal tasted so sweet.  I love my eggs really fresh, so my staff
has to try and coax the hens to lay while dangling them over a pot of
boiling water.  Sometimes I end up with hardboiled eggs, and sometimes it
turns out to be chicken soup.  Either way it's hard to beat.

The Mtv crew was surprised I didn't have bottles of Cristal in my fridge,
but suitably impressed that I do use it in my bidet.  We filmed a lot of
footage in my bedroom which apparently can only be legally broadcast in
Thailand.  I guess they were disappointed by my garage and my 1989 Ford
Escort, in spite of the horn which plays, "When The Levee Breaks" and
the fact that it sports a killer set of rims.

In the end, they offered me my own reality show but I think I'm going to
pass.  I do want to do an episode of Punk'd that will feature Ashton Kutcher
sucking off Diddy for a gram of coke, while Demi is lead around in just
heels and a dog collar to service his posse.  I know it doesn't sound like
much of a prank, but I already have the footage so it seems like a shame not
to use it?

The Perils of Pussy
>>> Casual Misanthropy

By staff writer Justin Rebello

May 8, 2005

Email article | Print-friendly | Send/read feedback (19) 
 


Articles | AIM | Bio
 
 

I hate cats.

(Well, what did you think the title meant? You should know by now I'm not above an obvious pun.)

Cats are a glaring, ugly, annoying waste of space, and they should be dragged out to the street one by one and beaten to death with a tire iron. There are two types of people: cat people and dog people. Dog people are intelligent, thoughtful beings, and cat people should be launched out of a cannon wearing their asshole as a helmet.


 
The seven reasons I hate cats, in no particular order:

1. They are ugly. Seriously, have you ever seen a cute cat? Kittens are cute, you say? You say wrong. Kittens are just like babies. Babies are not cute. They are pudgy and ugly and smell like the men's room at a gay bar. Kittens are even worse.

2. Cats think they are the shit. Seriously, if you ignore a dog, the dog comes after you and sniffs your crotch until you've got an erection and the phone number of a qualified therapist. A cat ignores YOU. Well, what the fuck? Who feeds you, asshole?

3. Cats are lazy. Can you play fetch with a cat? No, they lie around the house all day like friggin' Mexicans. Contributing nothing to society but pooping indoors. Just like Mexicans.

4. Litter boxes. I hate when people tell me cats are better because a cat is capable of dropping a deuce indoors. But let me get this straight, not only are you more than happy to let your pet drop some brown in the house, you'll allow them to play with it, and save it for later like a leftover calzone? What kind of logic is that? At least a dog knows his place.

5. Cats make shitty actors. I've seen a lot of great dog performances in my day: Old Yeller, Lassie, Benji, Shadow, Hooch, Puffy. Name one great cat performance? You can't. Cats are the Ashton Kutcher of animals: if you see them on a movie poster, you can pretty much attest the movie will suck.

6. Cats play with yarn. Isn't that a little fruity? Have you ever seen dog toys? Giant bones and rubber bouncy things. That's fun shit. I've bought myself a couple of dog toys that I play with constantly. Not like that. Perverts.

7. I'm allergic, so technically, they started it.

Cats. What gay animals.

you know what two GREAT words are? "fine" and "nothing"

for example:
how are you? "fine".      the person answering is most likely NOT fine, they are probably nowhere NEAR being fine. the great thing is, the word just seems to discourage further conversation, almost as if it is saying, "i am crappy, but i do not want to talk about it, so go away."

another example:
what happened?  "nothing."      it is obvious that something happened.  the person would not have been asking if it were not extremely obvious that something had happened. the answer, however, says something like, "lots of stuff happened, none of which i am prepared to talk about, least of all with YOU. screw off and leave me alone, please."

Finally, all of you, the masses of flesh and obedient slaves, subjective or objective, with no difference, you can feel the effect of tiding up modern arts on the Balkans. Every possibility of creative expression has been prohibited or at least made senseless because of general financial ignorance, useless because it is unprofitable. But when social-political conditions push creative art to the senseless, this is how I raise my own individual rebellion. 

No, we don't have idealistic approach suitable to neosatanist, who justify their behaviour explaining that they are big creator's kids who are destroying old to make new, the one who makes/changes by destroying... We don't want to create anything. We are destroying just to destroy. We are destroying 'cause we've been pushed to senselessness and we are trying to get out of it by destroying. Nothing can be changed. This is the end. And changing the flag won't save you. We don't have ideology and you cannot adjust to us. We are even between ourselves against one another.
We are destroying to destroy. We are destroying 'cause we are enjoying destroying. We tread by treading, we will trample you down by treading: You and your impotent "art" with national, regional or religious "values". 

Everyone, who would again expose pissoirs calling them fountains, or recite poetry with no existing words- he is called Repeating. He is commercializing and glorifying the senseless in senselessness. So, that's why I spit on your impotent "art" with national, regional of religious "values". 

















grace campbell had worked at the Burger Bust from over 13 years. Her promotion was coming up soon and she felt she had a shot. "Thirteen years!" she said. "They've gotta know what it takes to smell like recycled grease for thirteen years. I'm going to make assistant manager this time, I know it". She was confident that her movie career would take off any week now. From then on she would act as if Burger Bust never existed. All her friends she met working there, like Lydia, the widow. Frankie, the 20-something with down syndrome. Marl, the closet cowboy. She would abandon them all. After all, when she was a movie star, she could afford to buy another Frankie. 
The night went on and she decided to make another journal entry. 

"June 17, 1987", she wrote. "I'm going in early for my promotion tomorrow. If I don't get it, then there really is no reason to ever hope for a better life." She felt hot and covered in pins again. "You don't cry Grace," she told herself. "you save that for the movies". It was too late. She had crested the mountain of holding in her emotions and came rolling down the other side in a wheelbarrow of depression. She cried for a quarter of an hour and closed her journal for the night. "maybe TV might make me..." she thought. She walked into the den and flipped the lights. Her body froze for a tenth of a second, expecting someone else in there. There was no one. She knew there would be no one. "there never is...". Sitting down in the birds nest of a chair she bought from Pier One she tried to make herself comfortable, shifting this way, leaning that way. She finally got comfortable and dug the remote out from under her bony ass. The high pitched noise that came from the set let her know that the TV was on. She waited for the tube to warm up. She waited longer. Still longer. No picture. 

"Goddamn TV, you lasted me through the mom and dad's divorce, through high school", though her failed engagement she thought "and you want to start F##king up now?" 

She left the den of her apartment to fix a drink. It crossed her mind that she had thought about having a drink all day while at work. Before that even. Booze was on her mind from the moment she woke up to the last wheezing breath she took while conscious. "my author can't spell worth a damn," she though. "And his prose is pretentious, inconsistent at best." 

A shattering of glass hit cut though the air like a Lacey little Peterson. She dropped the Seagrams bottle she was holding, startled with fear

"What just happened?" she thought. "Did I just become aware of my own fictious existence?" She was in trouble now. Suddenly she felt nauseated, like a rag of chloroform on the face had been forced upon her. She saw the TV screen glowing but it was too blurry to make anything out... She dropped to her knees, then her head hit the floor. She lay there, amidst the broken glass for a few seconds... then, nothing... 

Someone else take it now. I'm tired. But then she suddenly rose to the sky and looked up, and what did she see.....I'll tell you....that she saw....

alright, before i get to the unimportant facts about my life that i am going to post, i will say that i am watching a crappy movie where a shirtless man who is only semi-hot runs around all sweaty with a knife, then hugs this equally sweaty girl, they lie down, and then someone comes along and kills them.

okay....went to melanie's halloween party, it was fun although we did not stay for the whole thing
then we went to dinner at nickels, where i did not eat anything. i do not like eating in restaurants, i go for the company. i was cold though, due to my halloween costume.

haha speaking of my costume...when i was standing at my busstop this morning, there was a guy there who i had never seen before. when i got outside he started talking to me about how i must be freezing, because it was verrrrry cold and i was in a dress that was not made with alot of material. i am happy, as i have never before been spoken to by a hot random (or at least not one who was not professing a hatred for me). i doubt it would have happened if i had been wearing more clothing, though.

i brought my whip to mel's, it was difficult to abstain from whipping the dog. not that i dont like the dog....i just reeally wanted to see what would happen haha

i am tired, i want to go to bed. i am staying up to watch the daily show, though.  happy news--i do not think i failed the physics test. yay. i'm  hungry, i have discovered that regardless of what i eat i will never be not hungry.

i had my pitchfork at school, i went around forking people. i love forking people, although being forked is equally, possibly more, enjoyable.
ttoday was interesting...well, tonight was, anyways. i feel rather violated, it is difficult to determine whether it is a good feeling or a bad feeling. i have very interesting friends.

yoga today was horrible, i cannot BREATHE properly and the rest of people in the chapel were laughing at the tape, which was rather annoying...then again, what am i supposed to do? yell, "hey, i'm meditating here?!!" wow i am a loser

this week, nancy became my hero...first she gave me cold pills so that i did not die of a head cold in BAND...then she lent be her giant yellow sweater for yoga (i forgot a yoga mat), so that i did not have to lie on the not-so-clean floor. 
then again, she also insulted my philosophizing...she read an (extremely crappy) entry in my philosophy journal that i wrote in french class, and told me that u was very good at making up bullshit. i chose to take that as a compliment, and not a negative comment on my philosophizing.

this week...i joined photography club, global outreach, and band....no wait i joined band last week..photography seems fun, except all of my friends seem to object to me being granted the use of a camera for parties etc...i suggest that my friends stop putting themselves in embarassing positions when i am there with a camera...global outreach seems, well, the same as last year, really....and band, well i have to move seats next time, as i cannot continue to sit next to the person i am sitting next to now without trying to beat her with my sax...of course, i cannot write her name, as it is a criminal offense for me to admit that i have such a burning hatred for the b*tch bass-clarinet player and may in the future try to beat her...

i am alternately looking forward to/dreading tomorrow...dreading, because i have a SHITLOAD of homework...and looking foward to because i have plans tomorrow night (see...i DO have a life)...but stilldreading ti because if i do not get enough work done i will not let me go do stuff...i do not know if that makes me self-disciplined, or just a loser.

arg...i do not like homework...but then again, perhaps i should have started it yesterday...meh oh well, instead of working i watched Confessions of a Teenage Drama Queen with jane & jamie, it was okay but entirely too unrealistic and kind of overdone:
1) girl moves to new city,
2) girl becomes friends with outcast,
3) together they hate the popular girls,
4)they convince parents to let them go to a concert to which they do not even have tickets,
5) friend finds out girl is a pathological liar,
6) they find the lead singer of the group they didn't get to see sitting drunk in an alley,
7) in return for finding him, he becomes their friend, they go to his party, he visits them at school, etc...
8) the popular girl is humiliated, but girl offers friendship--so everything works out in the end.  how classic.

on the bright side, though, i almost got in a fight on my way there...unfortunately, there were three of them and they looked rather angry (not to mention the less-than-polite things they were yelling), so i was at a considerable disadvantage....perhaps i should not rollerblade at night...

my grandmother and aunt are here visiting.  joy.

i am actually in a rather irritable mood...i am angry with several of my friends, mostly for stupid reasons such as that they are not here right now to keep me from being in a bad mood...

oh, and also, someone i used to stalk was wearing this horrible hat yesterday...and not only that, but he wa wearing it backwards...i lost a lot of liking for him because of that...well i suppose i should go start my crapload of work that i am not supposed to complain about because everyone else has the same amount of work but i want to complain anyways...

several things to write about today....the latest being that as i was unplugging my laptop to put it in a different room to use it, i accidentally touched one of the metal prongs...and received a minor electrical shock. minor as it may be, my index finger and all down my wrist on my right hand are tingly and very sore.

i also have discovered about myself that, although it takes a very long time for me to become friends with people, when i am friends with them i will have a sort of unshakable loyalty to them and a very strong need/desire to protect my friends from any sort of harm....and another thing i figured out is that i am helpless when my friends cry. i'm not saying i cant listen when people need someone to talk to, just that i don't do too well around tears...so when i am talking to someone, and they are upset about someone else, to the point where they cry...well, i am stuck with the helpless feeling of not knowing what to do to help my friend, and the overwhelming desire to find the bastard who did that and tear out his throat with my bare hands. its really not a good thing, i got a sort of nervous twitch today after seeing, several times, someone who i would love to take a hatchet to.

on a slightly more optimistic note, i feel like crap and am currently wallowing in a state of despair and misery, and it truly feels as though my life has gone to shit. i know i will feel more reasonable later, so do not bother commenting on my horrible mood...

also.....i will not be in school tomorrow (this is in no way connected to my crappy mood, by the way...i would not take a day off school just because i was in a bad mood. well,  at least not often.), so i will see/talk to y'all on wednesday.

i have learned that if you get a violent back massage by christie, then camille, then christina, then john, and then you sleep very oddly, you will wake up with horrible bakck and shoulder bruises... i have decided that i LOVE  that Vicks back/chest stuff that you rub on painful muscles to...well i dont know what it does..hurts less though.

went hottubbing today...twice, actually...i dyed my hair, too, but nobody seems to have noticed. it's not too diffeerent, so i suppose that's why. more news of how MORONIC i am, i have managed to misplace my buspass after only four days of school...HOPEFULLY, it is in my locker...

wellllll....now i am just sitting in my basement...watching tv...funfun.

oh, in other happy news (not), i am now expected to carry around a small joural with me at all times, and i am also expected to be struck with philosophical thoughts on a regular basis...and i must also write down these thoughts and reflect on them as they come.  i don't quite know how this is supposed to work, because so far in my life i have not found myself to be a particularly philosophical thinker.  arg.

school.....yuck
its too early, i think schools hould start at noon. grr.

i have french first (s'okay, needs mroe friends), philosophy (horrible because reitbauer dropped the class for GYM so i am stuck with gr 12s who i have decide all hate me), chem (okay, lots of writing by the looks of it), and physics (actually seems like itll be fun, theres lots of math).

i just attempted to start my chem homework, and to my disgust, i realized that the science textbook that i have is drastically different from last year's textbook...for one thing, there are almost NO PICTURES. thats just gross, how am i expected to pay attention to an uncolourful book with no pictures? i can tell this is going to be difficult

i am starting my stalking again already, actually, one of my stalking victims is in a class with me...haha little do you know i am watching you, my preeeeety...and from less than a metre away...

spent the weekend at my cottage with reitbauer...we took the boat out on sunday, and i was rather miserable as i had to first drive the boat far up enough so my dad could grab the rope, then jump in the waist-high freezing water to push it and steer it from behind-and all this while christina watched me from inside the boat. grr.

we also kind of sort of accidentally dropped an eighty pound slab of concrete and rocks onto christinas middle finger (on her right hand)...so it swelled up to about 2 or 3 times its normal size...and now she is claiming that i beat her, which is NOT TRUE, well not this time :P
actually...if anything, SHE beats ME...like one time, i was driving us on the boat, and she punched me! all i did was try to run over a seagull, and she punched me! how unfair is THAT?

we had the best, healithiest snack on saturday...fruit, covered in chocolate and coolwhip...mmmmm

i have discovered that, despite my paranoid obsessive applying sunscreen every time i set foot outdoors, i have a slight tan on my shoulders. luckily, the rest of me remains untanned.

i spent the last two hours or so assembling a drum set, because for reasons unbeknown to me my father decided to (temporarily) bring home a drum set from work.  i do not play drums. my mother does not play drums. my father does not play drums. my brother does not play drums. WHY do we need a drum set?
not even a complete drum set-it's missing one of the cymbals. the lack of a cymbal is more than made up for, however, by the fact that my father also brought home an electric guitar. needless to say, i was rather surprised to open a box that i believed to contain drums, only to pull out a guitar. my dad was a bit shocked as well, when i told him.

i truly think that my father is the only person capable of making such a mistake-forgetting a cymbal but replacing it with a spare guitar.

y'know those days where your mood is changing every ten minutes, like one second you're realizing how great your life is and how damn lucky you are, and the next you know that in the course of a day your whole life could end up blown to shit?

sometimes all it takes is the possibility of losing everything that makes you realize how much youve got, and how much you should appreciate it...im not trying to preach, or if i am then the only person i'm preaching to is myself...but i guess ive just figured lately that there are alot of people that i really love...you know who you are, and im so goddamned lucky to have all of you...

d'you ever feel like you wish things could stay exactly as they are forever, because you know that stuff's going to happen, maybe in a week or a month or whatever but you dont want it to so you just want to freeze your life, because it's not perfect but it's damn close and you like it, even the imperfections and the things that frustrate the hell out of you, they're all okay, all things you still want because...

it's familiar, its what you know...even if it's not the good stuff...it's the evil you know versus the evil youdon't know, stick with what you're used to, with the stuff you know how to fight... and what about when you're afraid of the future, not just worried or apprehensive but downright scared, the kind of scared that you fight to NOT let it keep you up at night, and you're scared of the things you don't know, of the variables-all of the things that could go wrong...

and when you think about it, think aabout all of the stuff that could go wrong, you realize the massive amount of potential time bombs waiting to explode and collapse your perfect world, the world you've built for yourself in such a way that you can just hide from all of this fear in the first place

but once you realize that you can't hide, what then? what if someone came and told you that this thing, the thing you're so scared of, has a date, a time, and a place, all set by people who are just living thier daily lives, who don't know of theeffect it's having on someone who stays up at night freaking out over this...thing.

and what about when you realize that the consequences of the thing NOT happening will, in the long term, be far worse than the possible consequences of it happening now? it's a choice of when you fiight it, and when you choose to could determine the severity of the fight, but you have no idea which is worse, and even if you did, what's it matter-none of this is up to you, you are entirely irrelevant in the whole thing, you're the preoverbail invalid-teh one in the hospital bed lying in a body cast--you can't move, can't speak...can't scream. all you can do is blink and watch the people around you make the decisions.

and maybe, you're lying there immobile and unable to move, watching it all unfold exactly how you don't want it to...but the people around you are experts, they know what they're doing...and it really doesn't take you much time for you to concede that they are people mokre suited to make decisions than you are, but that doesnt mean you like it...

doesn't mean you aren't still afraid of it.
